<li>For graphs, I use the <a href="http://www.ctan.org/tex-archive/graphics/pgf/">tikz</a> package. Jacques Crémer has written an excellent <a href="http://cremeronline.com/LaTeX/minimaltikz.pdf">mini-introduction</a> to tikz. <a href="http://www.hackenberger.at/blog/ktikz-editor-for-the-tikz-language/">qtikz</a> is a nice little software that makes graph creation with tikz even simpler by providing some WYSIWYG feeling.</li>
